<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10099347>
    dc:description "FIGURES 182–183. Mexalictus veracruzense Dumesh, n. sp., 182. Female lateral habitus, 183. Female head. Scale bars = 1mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10099347/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10099349>
    dc:description "FIGURE 184. Phylogeny of 26 Mexalictus species and two outgroup taxa (names as shown below) using 43 morphological characters with character state changes mapped onto the tree (Winclada, Nixon 2002). Black circles indicate uniquely derived character states, white circles indicate changes that are homoplasious elsewhere on the tree. See text for details of analysis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10099349/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10099351>
    dc:description "FIGURE 185. Phylogeny of Mexalictus edited with Mesquite (Maddison and Maddison, 2011) to show subgeneric separation of Mexalictus into Mexalictus (Georgealictus) (dark grey) and Mexalictus s. str. (light grey). Outgroups, Patellapis braunsella Michener and Thrincohalictus prognathus (Pérez) (black)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10099351/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

